According to a report by Intel Market Research, the India Quartz Fabrication Market was valued at USD 456 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 486 million in 2025 to USD 678 million by 2032, expanding at a CAGR of 6.8% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing strong momentum as rapid urbanization, expanding residential and commercial construction activities, and increasing consumer preference for premium interior materials continue to drive demand for engineered quartz products. The widespread adoption of advanced fabrication technologies, including CNC machining, waterjet cutting, and automated polishing systems, is further improving manufacturing efficiency, precision, and product quality, enabling companies to cater to evolving customer requirements across the country.
The growing popularity of engineered quartz in modern kitchens, bathrooms, flooring, wall cladding, and commercial interiors is significantly contributing to market growth. Compared to traditional materials such as granite and marble, engineered quartz offers superior durability, stain resistance, low maintenance, and a wide variety of design options, making it a preferred choice among architects, interior designers, builders, and homeowners. Rising disposable incomes, changing lifestyle preferences, and increasing investments in premium housing projects are further accelerating product adoption across India's metropolitan as well as Tier II and Tier III cities.
